**Fortune 2024 Spotlight: Automatic Data Processing (ADP) Climbs the Ranks**

In the latest Fortune 2024 ranking, Automatic Data Processing (ADP) has solidified its position as a leading player in the Business Services sector, specifically in the Diversified Outsourcing Services industry. With a ranking of 228, the company has demonstrated a notable improvement, gaining 23 places from its previous position.

Under the leadership of CEO Maria Black, who is also the company's first female CEO, ADP continues to exhibit a strong track record of profitability. Founded in 1949, the company has evolved to become a global provider of cloud-based human capital management solutions, with a diverse range of services catering to businesses of all sizes.

As of June 30, 2023, ADP boasts an impressive workforce of 63,000 employees, underscoring its commitment to job growth and development. This growth is further reflected in the company's revenue performance, with a 9.2% increase in revenues to $18.012 billion. Notably, ADP's profits have also seen a significant surge, rising by 15.7% to $3.412 billion.

The company's market value, as of March 28, 2024, stands at an impressive $102.591 billion, demonstrating its strong financial standing. ADP's assets, valued at $50.971 billion, provide a solid foundation for its continued growth and expansion.

As a publicly traded company, ADP is listed under the ticker symbol ADP, and its headquarters is located in Roseland, New Jersey. The company's commitment to excellence has earned it a spot on the prestigious list of the World's Most Admired Companies.

As ADP continues to navigate the ever-evolving landscape of the Business Services sector, its focus on innovation, customer satisfaction, and employee growth is expected to drive its future success. With its robust financial performance, strong leadership, and dedication to excellence, ADP is poised to maintain its position as a leading player in the industry.

**Key Statistics:**

Automatic Data Processing (ADP) is a U.S.-based company, founded in 1949, with its headquarters in Roseland, New Jersey. For more information, please visit their website at https://www.adp.com. The figures reported are for the fiscal year ended June 30, 2023, with market value as of March 28, 2024.